The paper deals with 3D reconstruction and alignment of partial scans, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The use of floorplan priors and the exploitation of the Manhattan World property suggest that the paper is likely to be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method also involves machine learning techniques for predicting room layouts, which could place the paper in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents a novel approach that enables some new applications, which could make it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) community as well.
